{
  "stem": "9730.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that when I met him, and he came to our regimental headquarters, he saw that I had a camera.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he-- he-- he said to me, wait, wait, let me adjust my-- my trench coat, and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If I had known you were going to take pictures of me today, I would have worn a better uniform.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And he-- he was quite congenial.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we-- we were, of course, taught to some degree, you know, how-- also how not to ask questions so that we-- we were able to compile, usually from a number of prisoners, what we-- what we were immediately looking for that would make our-- our troops' lives a little safer and-- and better, and also to effectively knock them out.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For instance, we would find out where their observation posts were and-- and, you know-- and where-- where some of their troops were-- were, you know, reinforcing certain lines.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew that if there was concentration, a heavier concentration of troops, we knew that there they were doing something either in a defensive position or possibly for-- for offense.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so-- so you learned, you know, how to ask the right questions.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And by-- also by finding out what units they were with, you knew, for instance, what-- what troops the Germans had had to-- to bring in, say, from another front, even from the Russian front sometimes, because once in a while, we would discover a new unit that we knew wasn't supposed to be there.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then we-- then we knew they were reinforcing their lines from that, or that they had had so many losses that they had to bring in other reinforcements.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it-- it-- to-- to varying degrees.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
